definition:
παρ-εμ-βολή, -ῆς, ἡ
 (παρεμβάλλω), [in LXX chiefly for מַחֲנֶה ;] 
  1. an insertion, interpolation (Æschin.) 
   2. In the Macedonian dialect (Rutherford, NPhr., 473), as a military term; 
   (a) an army in battle array: Heb.11:34 (cf. Exo.14:19-20, Jdg.4:16, al.; frequently in Polyb.); 
   (b) a camp (Exo.29:14, al.) : Heb.13:11, 13 Rev.20:9; 
   (with) barracks, soldiers' quarters: Act.21:34, 37 22:24 23:10, 16 23:32 28:16 (WH, txt., R, om.).†
 παρ-εμ-βάλλω, 
 [in LXX frequently and chiefly for מַחֲנֶה ;] 
  1. to put in beside or between, interpose. 
   2. In late writers (Polyb., al., LXX) as technical military term; 
   (a) of soldiers, to draw up in line (frequently in 1Ma.2:32, al.); 
   (b) of siege works, to cast up: with accusative and dative, χάρακά σοι, Luk.19:43.†
 (AS)
